# Raw screen-recording source files for README GIFs. The optimized
# .png stills in docs/images/ are committed; the multi-MB .MOV/.mp4
# source captures are not.
*.MOV
*.mov
*.mp4
*.m4v

# README GIFs are hosted as GitHub release assets (the "readme-assets"
# release), not committed, to keep the multi-MB animated binaries out of
# git history. The README references their release-download URLs. Keep
# the local copies in docs/images/crumble/ as the source-of-truth for
# re-uploading if they ever need to be regenerated.
docs/images/crumble/*.gif
